title: ASX to open higher after Fed
summary: Australian stock are poised to advance after the US central bank cut rates and signalled a pause going forward.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to fall; Woolworths, CPI ahead
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower, following cautious trading overseas, as investors await the Federal Reserve's US interest rate outlook.
author: Timothy Moore

title: S&P 500 closes at record high, ASX to rise
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher, bolstered by a tech rally on Wall Street that paced the S&P 500 to its highest ever.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise on positive US-China trade talk
summary: Australian shares are poised to extend last week's 1.3 per cent advance, buoyed by US-China trade truce hopes.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, $A slides
summary: Australian shares poised to open higher, potentially extending gains into a fifth session. The currency however slid 0.5%.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Wall St edge higher
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher as Wall Street regained some upward momentum late in its session.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, S&P 500 edges down
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower, following modest losses on Wall Street. The currency dipped.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, S&P 500 nears record
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher, bolstered by renewed hopes of a trade deal between the US and China.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX set to dip as big week of economic data looms
summary: Investors are in for another busy week of corporate earnings, including McDonald's on Tuesday, Boeing and Microsoft on Wednesday, and Amazon on Thursday.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to open lower as Brexit rally is shortlived
summary: Australian shares are set to open lower despite positive movement on Wall Street and a final breakthrough deal on Brexit.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX set to edge lower amid continued uncertainty over China, Brexit

author: Natasha Rudra

summary: Australian shares are set to lift as markets rallied on positive earnings reports on Wall Street and further optimism over Brexit.

title: ASX set to rise as partial trade deal sealed
summary: Australian shares are set to rise after the announcement of a partial trade deal between China and the US triggered a rally in markets.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX set to lift as hopes rise for partial US-China deal
summary: Australian shares are set to lift as global markets rallied at glimmers of positivity from US-China trade talks and Brexit negotiations.
author: Natasha Rudra

summary: Australian shares are poised to follow Wall Street's lead and open higher, amid hints the US and China are keen to secure at least a partial trade deal.

summary: Australian shares are set to open sharply lower as the prospects of progress on trade talks between the US and China turned south. The IMF sees danger ahead.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Wall St stalls

author: Timothy Moore

summary: A solid pace of US jobs growth has bolstered the case for lower rates as well as risk assets in general, including Australian shares. The $A has advanced, too.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, with US rate cut bets
summary: Australian shares are poised to close the week on a positive note, amid a surge in bets for an October US interest rate cut.
author: Timothy Moore

author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to drop, global manufacturing stalls

author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, RBA decision day
